    "narrative": "For the April 25th slate, our primary offensive anchors are **Cal Raleigh** (70.13) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (69.13), both of whom benefit from favorable matchups against pitchers with xERAs above 4.40. **Cal Raleigh**\u2019s position in the #2 hole combined with a strong platoon advantage against Liberatore makes him our safest high-ceiling play. Similarly, **Geraldo Perdomo**\u2019s elite 19% SP skill multiplier against M\u00e1rquez creates a high-floor outcome, maximizing our opportunity for stolen bases in a matchup that favors aggressive baserunning. While **Taylor Ward** faces a tough arm in Crochet, his elevated park factor and #1 spot in the order keep his score at a respectable 59.23, though he remains a volatility risk compared to the stability of **Will Smith**, whose 68.08 score hinges on favorable wind conditions and a solid matchup against Rea.\n\nStrategic benching remains critical to our 5x5 objectives, particularly regarding stolen base efficiency. The most difficult exclusion today was **Yainer Diaz**, who posted a 51.72 score but ultimately fell behind due to a projected #8 lineup spot, which significantly suppresses his run-production potential compared to the rest of the starting nine. **Jonathan Aranda** and **Bryson Stott** continue to be prioritized for their platoon-adjusted upside; **Bryson Stott**\u2019s 13% platoon boost against Elder proves more valuable than the fringe upside offered by **Gleyber Torres** or **Wenceel Perez**, neither of whom could crack the top-tier efficiency required today. \n\nRisk management for this afternoon centers on our exposure to Crochet and Gausman. While **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** is an elite talent, his 59.86 score is tempered by a poor BvP history against Gausman, requiring us to manage his performance expectations closely. Meanwhile, **Daulton Varsho** (45.72) and **Jeremiah Jackson** (45.71) are sitting on the razor's edge of our bench threshold; while their park factors are beneficial, the SP skill delta against Crochet forces them into a marginal tier. We will be monitoring the final lineups closely, as any shift away from our assumed batting order for **Will Smith** or **Bryson Stott** could necessitate an immediate re-evaluation of their daily efficiency scores.",
